 Abuja(SundiataPost) -The university of Ilorin alumni Association (FCT Capitol Assembly) will be holding her 2018 alumni reunion of the Better by Far University with a bang as the event is set to hold by the pool side of the BMT Gardens, Wuse II, Abuja on the 8th of December. The Permanent Secretary; General Services in the office of the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Barr. Olusegun Adekunle, who is also the Abuja Chapter Chairman of the alumni association, at a pre-event chat, disclosed that this year’s event will have only one awardee unlike in the past events. According to him, a teacher of teachers, literary icon, poet, scholar and sole winner of the 2018 Nigerian National Order of Merit (NNOM) Humanities Category, Prof. Olu Obafemi; will be specially recognized and honoured at this epoch making event. Mr. Adekunle, concluded that the reunion serves as homecoming for every alumni of the University of Ilorin in the FCT and its environs, so therefore, guests from within and outside the University of Ilorin community are expected at the occasion including distinguished alumnus and former Vice Chancellor, Prof. Ishaq Oloyede, National President of the alumni association; Dr Rhoda Oduwaiye, DG, Consumer Protection Council; Barr. Tunde Irukera as well as renown actor Barr. Tunji Bamisigbin amongst others. 